<ol><li>The browser <b>makes a request</b> to a web server to load a standard web page and all its resources.</li><li>The web page HTML file contains some&nbsp;<b>Javascript</b>&nbsp;which is executed on the client side.</li><li>The browser Javascript&nbsp;<b>calls the RESTful API</b>&nbsp;which enables communication with the server-side database using HTTP requests.</li><li>The database server <b>responds to the client's HTTP request</b> with the data in JSON or XML format.</li><li>The browser renders the JSON or XML data in its own <b>user interface</b>.</li></ol>